HEADWORD: Potting
<hw>Pot"ting</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Tippling.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The act of placing in a pot; <as>as, the
<ex>potting</ex> of plants; the <ex>potting</ex> of meats for
preservation.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The process of putting sugar in casks for cleansing
and draining.</def> <mark>[West Indies]</mark> <rj><au>B.
Edwards.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pottle</ent>⟦br⟧
